title: Anatomy 101 (2015).epub Gooner
description:
Anatomy 101 - From Muscles and Bones to Organs and Systems, Your Guide to How the Human Body Works (2015).epub Gooner

Publisher: Adams Media (July 4, 2015)
Language: English
ISBN-10: 1440584265
ISBN-13: 978-1440584268

An all-in-one guide to the human body!

Anatomy 101 offers an exciting look into the inner workings of the human body. Too often, textbooks turn the fascinating systems, processes, and figures of anatomy into tedious discourse that even Leonardo Da Vinci would reject. This easy-to-read guide cuts out the boring details, and instead, provides you with a compelling lesson in anatomy. Covering every aspect of anatomical development and physiology, each chapter details the different parts of the human body, how systems are formed, and disorders that could disrupt bodily functions. You'll unravel the mysteries of anatomy with unique, accessible elements like:

* Detailed charts of each system in the body
* Illustrations of cross sections
* Unique profiles of the most influential figures in medical history

From cell chemistry to the respiratory system, Anatomy 101 is packed with hundreds of entertaining facts that you can't get anywhere else!
